        "title": "2. `filters.py` — regex word-boundary edge cases untested",
        "content": "\n**Gaps:** `include`/`exclude` interaction order (exclude wins when both match), word-boundary matching for punctuation-adjacent keywords (e.g. \"C++\", \"ML/AI\"), `cutoff` behavior on unparseable dates (must **keep**, not drop — that's a documented deliberate choice worth locking in), empty `rules` dict.\n\n```python\n",
