        "title": "--- bytedance location chain walk ----------------------------------------",
        "content": "def test_bd_location_walks_parent_chain():\n    city = {\"en_name\": \"Seattle\", \"parent\": {\"en_name\": \"WA\", \"parent\": {\"en_name\": \"USA\"}}}\n    assert _bd_location(city) == \"Seattle, WA, USA\"\n\ndef test_bd_location_handles_none():\n    assert _bd_location(None) == \"\"\n\ndef test_bd_location_missing_names_in_middle_of_chain():\n    city = {\"parent\": {\"en_name\": \"USA\"}}  # city itself has no name\n    assert _bd_location(city) == \"USA\"\n```\n\n**Deduplication gap:** `parse_meta` dedupes on `jid` internally (`seen` set) but no other parser does, and none of that de-dup logic is tested anywhere — worth one test per parser that dedupes.\n\n```python\ndef test_parse_meta_dedupes_by_id():\n    from fetchers import parse_meta\n    results = [{\"id\": \"1\", \"title\": \"A\"}, {\"id\": \"1\", \"title\": \"A-dup\"}]\n    jobs = parse_meta(\"meta\", results)\n    assert len(jobs) == 1\n```\n\n",
        "level": 1
